text.__SUMMARY__:
Acacia nana is a shrub belonging to the genus Acacia and the subgenus Phyllodineae where it is endemic to eastern Australia.
The shrub typically grows to a height of 0.2 to 2 m (7.9 in to 6 ft 6.7 in) and has reddish to brown branchlets and straight narrowly elliptic to oblanceolate shaped phyllodes.
It is native to a disjunct area in the northern and central tablelands of New South Wales.
